🐧🐧🐧 Get ready, Southend-on-Sea! The city is being taken over by an adorable army of penguins! 🐧🐧🐧

"Waddle-on-Sea" has officially launched, bringing over 30 super-sized penguin sculptures and 70+ baby penguins to our streets for a flipping fabulous public art trail! Each one is uniquely designed and promises to bring colour and fun to your summer.

➡️ When to catch them: These magnificent birds will be waddling around Southend from Friday, July 11th to Wednesday, September 3rd, 2025.

📲 Don't get in a muddle, follow the huddle! To make sure you don't miss a single one, download the official Waddle-on-Sea app from the App Store or Google Play. It's your ultimate guide to the trail, with maps, sculpture listings, design inspiration, and even rewards!

This incredible event, brought to you by Havens Hospices and Wild in Art, isn't just about art; it's about raising vital funds for Havens Hospices' specialist palliative care. So come explore, enjoy the art, and support a fantastic cause! 

#WaddleOnSea #Southend #PenguinArtTrail #HavensHospices #SupportLocal

latestPosts.caption:
🌿 Estonian folk ensemble RÜÜT returns with their summer single “Kiigun üle mäe” - a tender ode to white nights, forest air, and a thousand summer mosquitoes.

💬 “Some songs come to you in the most unexpected places - and end up being the most heartfelt,” shares songwriter Maili Metssalu.

🎥 Filmed on Paluküla Hiiemägi with a local folk dance group, the romantic video captures Estonia’s quiet midsummer magic.

After winning 3 Etnokulp awards and releasing their acclaimed album “Kiriküüt”, RÜÜT continues to expand what modern folk can be.

“Kiigun üle mäe” is out now on all streaming platforms! 🎧

#music #estonia #newmusic #newrelease #RÜÜT
